text.tspan: Icons should be submitted as a square
This kit was made to help people put together icons that are consistant with the Ubuntu
phone suru design language. It comes with grids and paper folds for easy uses.
Please look at the Ubuntu phone design guidelines. Url at the top. Feel free to report
issues or contribute to the kit at https://github.com/halfsail/Ubuntu-UI-Tookit
For preview what your icon will look like
They can be submitted as 512x512 but will be downsized to 256x256
Most of the core apps have a subtle diagonal gradient or simple flat background
Folds have been simplified in 15.10 to a plain white square at 15%-10% opacity.
